There once lived a young lass named Kit Tyler, who dwelled freely upon sun-drenched Barbados, and though her life there was joyous, the passing of her beloved grandfather forced her to sail far across the sea. She arrived in the stark Puritan colony of Wethersfield, seeking kin, but found a cold, unyielding world vastly different from her own. There, Kit's spirited nature and vibrant ways clashed with the settlers' strict customs, marking her as an outsider. Thus, she sought solace in the wild Meadows, where she befriended an old woman named Hannah Tupper, whom the townsfolk shunned as a witch. Yet, this bond of friendship, misunderstood and feared, slowly drew suspicion upon Kit herself, leading her toward a perilous accusation.
